You need:
* Python 2.6+
* Twisted 10+
* zope.interface
* MySQLdb 1.2.3 (or pymysql)
* cjson/usjon/simplejson
* pywin32 if you intend to use IOCP (default on windows)
* setuptools / python distribute to compile the cryptomodule

You also need to compile otcrypto:
python setup.py build # You can also choose install here, but it might conflict on some systems
cp build/*/*.so core

There is a precompiled version inside the WINDOWS folder.

Links for Windows:
http://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.2/python-2.7.2.msi
http://www.codegood.com/download/10/
http://twistedmatrix.com/Releases/Twisted/11.0/Twisted-11.0.0.winxp32-py2.7.msi
http://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/pywin32/pywin32/Build216/pywin32-216.win32-py2.7.exe?r=http%3A%2F%2Fsourceforge.net%2Fprojects%2Fpywin32%2Ffiles%2Fpywin32%2FBuild216%2F&ts=1310085256&use_mirror=netcologne
And grab:
zope.interface-3.7.0.win32-py2.7.exe
and
Base-11.X.YY.win32-py2.7.exe (X = a month and YY = a day, this package gets updated all the time!)
from:
http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/ (This site also got 64bit editions of most of the libs except mysqldb, which you can get on codegood if you really need it)

Archlinux:
pacman -S python2 mysql-python twisted python-cjson python-distribute

Ubuntu (10.04+):
apt-get install python-twisted python-setuptools python-cjson python-mysqldb python2.7 (might need to install 2.6 here!)
